<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12952] AlterTableStatement propagates base table and affected MV changes inconsistently</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12952</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;AlterTableStatement&lt;/tt&gt;, when renaming columns or changing their types, we also keep track of all affected MVs - ones that also need column renames or type changes. Then in the end we announce the migration for the table change, and afterwards, separately, one for each affected MV.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This creates a window in which view definitions and base table definition are not in sync with each other. If a node fails in between receiving those pushes, it&apos;s likely to have startup issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is trivial: table change and affected MV change should be pushed as a single schema mutation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
